The '''Greater Mark of Illumination''' was a symbol of the [[Chalactan Adepts/Legends|Chalactan Adepts]], one of the [[Mark of Illumination/Legends|Marks of Illumination]]. A [[Gold/Legends|gold]] bead, it symbolized the universe and the [[Uncloseable Eye]] that saw it, and was given to those who achieved the [[Chalactan Enlightenment]] by the [[Convocation of Adepts]]. It was permanently affixed to the frontal bone of the Adept's skull, and was a larger version of the [[Lesser Mark of Illumination|Lesser Mark]].

One person who attained enlightenment was the [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Depa Billaba/Legends|Depa Billaba]]. However, the [[Summertime War]] of [[Haruun Kal/Legends|Haruun Kal]] greatly warped her beliefs, and she removed the bead eventually, leaving a scar.

